es’, we must revisit the civil liberties arguments of its defender, Morris Ernst</h1><p class="sc-a817e74d-5 iWngXi">by <!-- -->Brett Gary<!-- --> <span class="toggleMobileCreditBtn">+ BIO</span></p></div></div></div><div align="right" class="sc-80692d4-3 kfZhqg"><small class="sc-80692d4-4 izlZNf"><p>James Joyce with his publisher Sylvia Beach in her bookstore, Shakespeare and Company, in Paris, 1922. Photo by Getty Images</p></small></div></div></div><div class="sc-3d907c20-0 hVinCK"><div class="sc-3d907c20-5 cpKVLZ"><aside class="sc-3d907c20-12 cpiLGb"><div aria-hidden="true" class="rah-static rah-static--height-zero SidebarWrapper" style="height:0;overflow:hidden"><div><div class="sc-2e8621ab-0 jwmryO sc-3d907c20-7 dmZDGn"><a href="/users/brett-gary" class="sc-2e8621ab-1 jexetL">Brett Gary</a><span><p>is associate professor of media, culture and communication at NYU. He is the author of <a href="http://cup.columbia.edu/book/the-nervous-liberals/9780231113656" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener"><em>The Nervous Liberals: Propaganda Anxieties from World War One to the Cold War</em></a> (1999) and <a href="https://www.sup.org/books/title/?id=33733" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener"><em>Dirty Works: Obscenity on Trial in America’s First Sexual Revolution</em></a> (2021).</p></span></div><br/><div class="sc-3d907c20-9 buzlSL"><p>Edited by<a href="/users/samdresser" class="sc-2e8621ab-1 jexetL">Sam Dresser</a></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-114c07c9-0 iNdsQY"><span>3,500<!-- --> words</span><span class="sc-114c07c9-1 bvsiTx"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" width="16" height="16" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" data-cy="icon-aeon-comment-bubble"><path d="M21.303,16.553l1.107,3.783l-3.48-2.322c-0.689,0.234-1.422,0.371-2.193,0.371c-1.041,0-2.024-0.234-2.907-0.642 c2.034-1.697,3.333-4.275,3.333-7.166c0-1.994-0.625-3.836-1.677-5.347c0.406-0.073,0.823-0.117,1.251-0.1